stupidmodel.agents
Class Predator

java.lang.Object
  stupidmodel.agents.Predator

public class Predator
extends java.lang.Object

In Model 16, we have a new agent type for predators.

Predator agents have a really simple behaviour: they start random walking on the grid, and as soon as they find a Bug agent, they eat it and move to their position. All of the predator actions are scheduled after the Bug actions.

Since predator agents are actually very simple, they are visualized with the DefaultStyleOGL2D offered by the wizard on the graphical user interface.

Method Detail

hunt

public void hunt()
Predators move randomly and search for bugs in their surroundings. If they find the first, the found Bug agent is killed and they move to the location of the killed Bug.

Scheduled after all the Bug actions.

                             repast.simphony.query.space.grid.GridCell<HabitatCell> cell,

Utility function for Predator agents to determine if a given cell whether has an agent from a specified type located at or not.

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the agent we are searching for at the specified location
Parameters:
grid - the grid on which the Predator agent is located at; should not be null
cell - the cell where specified agent type is searched; should not be null
clazz - the Class<T> object of the agent we are searching for
Returns:
true if the number of agent instances from the specified type at the given location is above zero; false otherwise
